title: Eps. 148 - The Miserable Millionaire
description:
If your a sports fan you know that recently the Boston Red Sox won the world series again. There’s an interesting fact that there is only one player on the team who was a part of the team the last time it won the World Series in 2013. What does that mean ? It means that being a part of a winning culture can be a game changer in your life. A winning culture can and will help you perform at your highest level if you welcome the challenge. Assess your culture of friends, mentors, and colleagues. Is it a culture that promotes greatness or a culture that helps you make excuses for being average ?
